In the project at `/tmp/sv-1d5e08e4cf15476395337ad749bf2f96/before/`, replace ALL occurrences of `JsonSerializer.Serialize(writer, document.RootElement)` with `document.RootElement.WriteTo(writer)` in every `.cs` file.

These appear inside `#else` blocks like:
```csharp
#if NET6_0_OR_GREATER
    writer.WriteRawValue(item.Value);
#else
    using (JsonDocument document = JsonDocument.Parse(item.Value, ModelSerializationExtensions.JsonDocumentOptions))
    {
        JsonSerializer.Serialize(writer, document.RootElement);
    }
#endif
```

The replacement is mechanical: just change `JsonSerializer.Serialize(writer, document.RootElement)` → `document.RootElement.WriteTo(writer)`.

Use grep to find all occurrences, then edit each file. Do NOT add any new using statements - `WriteTo` is a method on `JsonElement` from `System.Text.Json` which is already imported in these files.

